        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:55PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Isolated to widely scattered showers and thunderstorms were moving
to the northeast at approximately 20 mph. While these showers and
thunderstorms have generally been producing gusty and erratic wind
gusts of between 25 mph and 35 mph a few of the strongest storms
could produce wind gusts in excess of 45 mph. Those recreating
outdoors should be prepared to seek shelter should storms
approach.
</description>
